snippet: In recent clashes, at least 71 people were killed and more than 300 were wounded, the World Health Organization said Thursday.
abstract: Clashes in Somali port city of Kismayu between rival clans have killed at least 71 people and wounded more than 300; clans are vying for power after Islamist militants withdrew from city in 2012.
lead_paragraph: In recent clashes, at least 71 people were killed and more than 300 were wounded, the World Health Organization said Thursday.

headline.main: Despite Exit of Militants, Violence Continues to Grip Somali City and Raises Worries
headline.print_headline: Despite Exit of Militants, Violence Continues to Grip Somali City and Raises Worries
